rest_of_day_open: During the rest of my week, I see myself training to be a cook in my new position at work. I see my week ending with a lot of hours at work and less relaxation time. During this week, I will begin thinking about continuing college for my Master's degree and trying to organize different aspects in my life.
critical_positive: Carlos was very friendly and understanding. At the beginning, I was ready to have the 25 minute conversation over with, but as we talked more I began to appreciate his company and his advice. I did not expect the conversation to work out well because he was far older than I, but I found that the age difference gave us a different perspective on life.
critical_negative: I felt that I was not talkative enough. I was too engaged in the conversation and felt I didn't have much to offer. I thought I was going to be provided with a list of questions or conversation starters, so I was taken off guard when I found we would have to make up our own conversation.

rest_of_day_open: Today is Saturday so it is ending. I have to prepare a presentation and a poster by the 10, then a chapter by the 30. Dreading to be on the computer. I'll go for a long walk today. I'm spending the 4th of July alone, avoiding people and watching TV. There will be lots of opportunities to socialize when the pandemic is over!
critical_positive: I liked Shawn very much. Probably because she's young, sweet, and pretty, and she's a promising student. I felt specially compelled to like her because she's black. I know it's patronizing, but I feel that we owe them a lot. I'm not white, I'm Mexican, but I enjoy white privilege through my husband and the place I live. She probably thought I was some creepy dork giving her unsolicited advice, but I love giving advice to young people, I feel like oh I wish somebody had been nice to me when I was their age, so I start asking questions and giving unsolicited advice and telling young people reasons to feel good and happy about themselves. We didn't have much in common, other than a willingness to have a nice conversation. Well maybe both of us are a little loners. I just wanted her to feel safe and happy.
critical_negative:
